\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {RFT polishes consistency but spends the variance that sampling needs.} Judge-keep vs.\ number of samples on the $18$-task hard held-out suite for the chosen SFT student and the same student after RFT. RFT improves every per-turn consistency metric (\Cref  {tab:distill-rft}) yet regresses pass@$3$ by $17$\,pp: the near-tie at one sample and the flat curve past it show the lost quality is exactly the distributional spread best-of-$N$ converts into solved tasks.\relax }}{15}{figure.caption.37}\protected@file@percent }
